' Example of how to use SharpShell to create a simple shell extension (simplified)\n\nImports System.Runtime.InteropServices\nImports SharpShell.Attributes\nImports SharpShell.SharpContextMenu\n\n<ComVisible(True)>\n<COMServerAssociation(AssociationType.AllFiles)>\nPublic Class SimpleShellExtension\n    Inherits SharpContextMenu\n\n    Protected Overrides Function CreateMenu() As ContextMenuStrip\n        Dim menu = New ContextMenuStrip()\n        menu.Items.Add("Simple Command").AddClick(AddressOf SimpleCommand_Click)\n        Return menu\n    End Function\n\n    Private Sub SimpleCommand_Click(sender As Object, e As EventArgs)\n        MessageBox.Show("You clicked the simple command!")\n    End Sub\nEnd Class